div.h1: Selectivity: When Indexes Help vs Hurt

p.strong: Creating an index does NOT guarantee faster queries.

ol.li: How many rows match the predicate? (selectivity)
What's the cost of finding them via index?
What's the cost of scanning the table?

div.p: Sequential I/O (table scan) is faster than random I/O (index lookups) when you need to touch many rows.
Index lookup per row: ~10-25s (random I/O) Sequential page read: ~1s per row (batched)
